@NODE "WhatIsIt"

IconImageCopier is a program that will help you copy icon images between
icons.

Features:
· Supports OS2.0-OS3.5 and newicons
· Can copy one image to a lot of other icons easily
· Small
· Handles all types of icons and will only copy the icon image
· Can create icons for files without icons
· Can copy default icon's images as well
· Fully localized
· Few @{"bugs" LINK Bugs}

                            @{"System requirements" LINK SystemRequirements}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SystemRequirements"

To run IconImageCopier you need at least AmigaOS2.0. No special libraries
are needed.

                               @{"Installation" LINK Installation}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation"

Install the program by using the provided installer script. If you want to
do it yourself, simply copy the "IconImageCopier", "IconImageCopier.info",
"CopyImage.info" and "PasteImage.info" to the same place. Actually they
don't need to be in the same drawer but if they aren't you'll have to
specify where the copy and paste icons are (tooltypes or CLI-arguments).

                               @{"How to use it" LINK HowToUseIt}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HowToUseIt"

The program can be started from Workbench or CLI. When started the program
will add two appicons to the Workbench, one copy appicon and one paste
appicon. Drop one icon on the copy appicon and then that icon's image will
be read by the program. Note that you will not see anything happening now
(unless something went wrong). Now, to paste that image on other icons,
just drop them on the paste appicon. You may drop multiple icons at the
same time and may drop several single icons as well.

The default copy and paste icon path can be changed via tooltypes or
CLI-arguments as well as the text displayed under the appicons.
___________________________________________________________________________

The CLI-arguments are:

COPYIMAGE/K,PASTEIMAGE/K,COPYTEXT/K,PASTETEXT/K

The tooltypes are:

COPYIMAGE
PASTEIMAGE
COPYTEXT
PASTETEXT

and the meaning of it all:

COPYIMAGE:

This is the path to the file whose icon should be used as the copy image.
Note that the ".info" part should NOT be added to the filename. Defaults to
"CopyImage".

PASTEIMAGE:

This is the path to the file whose icon should be used as the paste image.
Note that the ".info" part should NOT be added to the filename. Defaults to
"PasteImage".

COPYTEXT:

This is the text that will be written under the copy appicon on the
Workbench. Defaults to "Copy".

PASTETEXT:

This is the text that will be written under the paste appicon on the
Workbench. Defaults to "Paste".
___________________________________________________________________________

Exit IconImageCopier by double-clicking on the copy or paste appicon and
then press the "Quit" button in the information requester. If you have
AmogaOS3.5 installed you can select the copy or paste appicon and then
select "Put away" from the workbench icon menu. You can also send CTRL-C to
the program if you know how to do that.

