                                   @{"Bugs" LINK Bugs}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Bugs"

If you use OS3.5 or later then you CAN copy a newicon image to another icon
BUT the destination icons will be converted to the OS3.5-native icon format
- not the newicon icon format.

If you use OS3.1 or earlier AND have newicon.library installed you can only
copy icon images from REAL icons to REAL icons, that is files, drawers or
disks with an associated .info file.

If you use OS3.1 or earlier and no newicon.library installed, any newicon
images will be left untouched - will not be copied and will not be removed.

